      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Aug. 20.--Yesterday\nafternoons session Of the Trans\nMississippi Commercial congress end\ned abruptly. owing to q rurnor that\nthe Seattle street car strike would be\non at 4 o'clock and the delegates did\nnot relish the idea Of walking In from\nLeschi park.\n\n\n1t having been practically decided\nto hold next years session at st.\nLouis, Richard c. Kerens Of Missouri\nwas elected president. Washington's\ncandidate. A. L. Black Of Whatcom,\nreceiving the first vice presidency.\n\n\nThe Washington delegation Is con-\ncentrating it's efforts upon securing\nthe endorsement Of congress Of res\nolution providing for the preservation\nOf forests from fire by some ade-\nquate national legislation.\n\n\nMontana wants the repeal of the\ndesert land act. the Communication\nclause Of the homestead act and the\ntimber and stone act. and opposing\nthe leasing Of public lands for range\npurposes. Sc"
